&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;How can I tell whether a tour is genuinely &quot;green&quot;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;A genuine green tour in line with the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Green Travel Guide: Protecting Cat Ba&#039;s Forests and Seas with Small Actions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; will have a clear itinerary regarding conservation, will not intrude on restricted areas, will use local guides who understand the environment, and will have strict waste-management policies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Why shouldn&#039;t you feed the animals in Cat Ba&#039;s forest?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Feeding animals causes them to lose their instincts for hunting and foraging for natural food. Moreover, human food may contain pathogens or ingredients harmful to the health of the rare primate species protected under the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Green Travel Guide: Protecting Cat Ba&#039;s Forests and Seas with Small Actions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
